'''Nélson Cabral Semedo''' (born 16 November 1993) is a Portuguese professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Defender (association football)#Full-back|right-back]] or [[right wing-back]] for [[Süper Lig]] club [[Fenerbahçe S.K. (football)|Fenerbahçe]] and the [[Portugal national football team|Portugal national team]].

Semedo began his career at [[S.U. Sintrense|Sintrense]] before joining [[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]] in 2012. After spending a season on loan at [[C.D. Fátima|Fátima]], he initially appeared for [[S.L. Benfica B|Benfica B]] before making his first-team debut in 2015 and going on to win back-to-back [[Primeira Liga]] titles, among other honours. In July 2017, he signed with [[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]], winning [[La Liga]] in his first two seasons of a three-year stay. In September 2020, Semedo moved to [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton Wanderers]].

Semedo made his senior debut for [[Portugal national football team|Portugal]] in October 2015 and represented the nation at the [[2017 FIFA Confederations Cup]], [[2019 UEFA Nations League Finals]], [[UEFA Euro 2020]], and [[UEFA Euro 2024]].

==Club career==
===Benfica===
Born in [[Lisbon]], Semedo came through the youth system at [[S.U. Sintrense|Sintrense]], making his debut for the first team at age 17.<ref name=OC>{{cite web|url=https://aoutravisao.wordpress.com/2015/06/09/olho-clinico-nelson-semedo/|title=Olho Clínico – Nélson Semedo|trans-title=Clinical eye – Nélson Semedo|publisher=A Outra Visão|language=pt|date=9 June 2015|access-date=25 June 2015}}</ref> On 12 January 2012, he and [[Manuel Liz]] signed five-year contracts with [[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]] which were made effective on 1 July 2012.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.slbenfica.pt/noticias/detalhedenoticia/tabid/2788/articleid/20660/detalhedenoticia.aspx|title=Mais dois jovens talentos no Benfica|trans-title=Two more young talents to Benfica|publisher=S.L. Benfica|language=pt|date=12 January 2012|access-date=25 June 2015|archive-date=22 August 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170822095401/http://www.slbenfica.pt/noticias/detalhedenoticia/tabid/2788/articleid/20660/detalhedenoticia.aspx|url-status=dead}}</ref> Both then spent [[2012–13 Segunda Divisão|one season]] on loan at [[C.D. Fátima|Fátima]] in the [[Portuguese Second Division|third division]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.agentedesportivo.com/ii-divisao-sul-nelson-semedo-e-manuel-liz-reforcam-o-fatima/|title=Manuel Liz e Nélson Semedo emprestados ao Fátima|trans-title=Manuel Liz and Nélson Semedo loaned to Fátima|publisher=Agente Desportivo|language=pt|date=9 August 2012|access-date=13 December 2015|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151222140001/http://www.agentedesportivo.com/ii-divisao-sul-nelson-semedo-e-manuel-liz-reforcam-o-fatima/|archive-date=22 December 2015}}</ref>

Semedo returned to Benfica in the 2013 off-season, being assigned to the [[S.L. Benfica B|B-side]] in the [[Segunda Liga]] and making his professional debut on 10 August in a 0–0 away draw against [[C.D. Trofense|Trofense]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/2--liga/detalhe/trofense-benfica-b-0-0-nulo-no-arranque-838049.html|title=Trofense-Benfica B, 0–0: Nulo no arranque|trans-title=Trofense-Benfica B, 0–0: Draw to kickstart it|newspaper=[[Record (Portuguese newspaper)|Record]]|language=pt|date=10 August 2013|access-date=22 August 2017|archive-date=22 August 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170822133421/http://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/2--liga/detalhe/trofense-benfica-b-0-0-nulo-no-arranque-838049.html|url-status=dead}}</ref> After nearly 60 appearances for the reserves, he was touted as a future replacement for long-time first-team incumbent [[Maxi Pereira]].<ref name="OC"/><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.record.xl.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/liga-nos/benfica/detalhe/nelson-semedo-visto-como-solucao-para-o-futuro-934663.html|title=Nélson Semedo visto como solução para o futuro|trans-title=Nélson Semedo seen as future solution|newspaper=Record|language=pt|date=5 March 2015|access-date=13 December 2015|archive-date=26 December 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151226042255/http://www.record.xl.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/liga-nos/benfica/detalhe/nelson-semedo-visto-como-solucao-para-o-futuro-934663.html|url-status=dead}}</ref>

[[File:Zenit-Benf (8).jpg|thumb|left|Semedo playing for Benfica in the [[UEFA Champions League]]]]

After Pereira's departure, Semedo extended his contract until 2021 and joined the first team on their pre-season tour in North America in July 2015.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.record.xl.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/liga-nos/benfica/detalhe/nuno-santos-nelson-semedo-raphael-guzzo-e-joao-teixeira-renovam-961982.html|title=Nélson Semedo: "Não estava à espera"|trans-title=Nélson Semedo: "I wasn't expecting it"|newspaper=Record|language=pt|date=13 July 2015|access-date=5 December 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151208143648/http://www.record.xl.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/liga-nos/benfica/detalhe/nuno-santos-nelson-semedo-raphael-guzzo-e-joao-teixeira-renovam-961982.html|archive-date=8 December 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref> On 9 August 2015, he made his debut for the main squad in the [[2015 Supertaça Cândido de Oliveira|0–1 loss]] against [[Sporting CP]] for the [[Supertaça Cândido de Oliveira]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.ojogo.pt/futebol/1a-liga/benfica/noticias/interior/nelson-semedo-titular-4722300.html|title=Nélson Semedo titular|trans-title=Nélson Semedo starts|newspaper=[[O Jogo]]|language=pt|date=9 August 2015|access-date=5 December 2015|archive-date=9 August 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170809092237/http://www.ojogo.pt/futebol/1a-liga/benfica/noticias/interior/nelson-semedo-titular-4722300.html|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rtp.pt/noticias/desporto/supertaca-e-do-sporting_e850342|title=Benfica 0–1 Sporting|publisher=[[Rádio e Televisão de Portugal]]|language=pt|date=9 August 2015|access-date=22 August 2017}}</ref> A week later, he scored his first goal for them, against [[G.D. Estoril Praia|Estoril]] in the [[Primeira Liga]] in a 4–0 home win.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://desporto.sapo.pt/futebol/primeira_liga/artigo/2015/08/16/veja-o-golo-de-nelson-semedo|title=Veja o golo de Nélson Semedo|trans-title=Watch Nélson Semedo goal|publisher=SAPO|language=pt|date=16 August 2015|access-date=5 December 2015}}</ref>

After establishing himself in the starting 11, Semedo suffered a setback in October 2015 when he sustained an injury while with the Portugal national team.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.record.xl.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/liga-nos/benfica/detalhe/nelson-semedo-regressou-lesionado-980566.html|title=Nélson Semedo regressou lesionado|trans-title=Nélson Semedo returned injured|newspaper=Record|language=pt|date=13 October 2015|access-date=5 December 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151208174015/http://www.record.xl.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/liga-nos/benfica/detalhe/nelson-semedo-regressou-lesionado-980566.html|archive-date=8 December 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref> The ailment to his right knee required surgery, with him being expected to miss two months.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://desporto.sapo.pt/futebol/primeira_liga/artigo/2015/10/14/voltarei-mais-forte|title=Nélson Semedo: "Voltarei mais forte"|trans-title=Nélson Semedo: "I will return stronger"|publisher=SAPO|language=pt|date=14 October 2015|access-date=5 December 2015|archive-date=17 March 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160317123626/http://desporto.sapo.pt/futebol/primeira_liga/artigo/2015/10/14/voltarei-mais-forte|url-status=dead}}</ref> He returned to action in early January,<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/liga-nos/benfica/detalhe/nelson-semedo-espreita-chamada-para-o-estoril.html|title=Nélson Semedo espreita chamada para o Estoril|trans-title=Nélson Semedo eyeing call-up to Estoril|newspaper=Record|language=pt|date=15 January 2016|access-date=7 June 2017|archive-date=9 August 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170809043401/http://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/liga-nos/benfica/detalhe/nelson-semedo-espreita-chamada-para-o-estoril.html|url-status=dead}}</ref> but could not reproduce his previous form and lost his place to [[André Almeida (footballer, born 1990)|André Almeida]].<ref>{{cite magazine|title=O tricampeão voltou|trans-title=The three-time champions are back|magazine=[[Visão]]|language=pt|date=May 2016|page=34|issn=0872-3540}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|title=Benfica tricampeão|trans-title=Benfica back-to-back-to-back champions|newspaper=[[A Bola]]|language=pt|date=May 2016|isbn=978-989-8290-12-0|page=150}}</ref> Semedo finished the campaign in the reserve team.<ref>{{cite magazine|title=Tri glorioso|trans-title=Glorious tri|newspaper=Record|language=pt|date=17 May 2016|volume=13|issue=540|page=32|issn=0870-2179}}</ref>

In [[2016–17 Primeira Liga|2016–17]], Semedo regained his starting position and went on to be Benfica's third-most used player in the club's historic fourth-straight league title.<ref>{{cite book|title=Benfica tetracampeão|trans-title=Benfica back-to-back-to-back-to-back champions|newspaper=A Bola|language=pt|date=May 2017|isbn=978-989-8290-15-1|page=149}}</ref> He scored once in the league in a 2–1 win on the road over [[F.C. Arouca|Arouca]]<ref>{{cite book|title=Benfica tetracampeão|trans-title=Benfica back-to-back-to-back-to-back champions|newspaper=A Bola|language=pt|date=May 2017|isbn=978-989-8290-15-1|page=22}}</ref> and once in the [[UEFA Champions League]] in a [[2016–17 UEFA Champions League|3–3 group stage draw]] to [[Beşiktaş J.K.|Beşiktaş]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/match/2019357--besiktas-vs-benfica/|title=Second-placed Beşiktaş keep knockout hopes alive with sensational comeback|publisher=UEFA|date=21 November 2016|access-date=7 June 2017}}</ref>

In [[2017 Taça de Portugal Final|the final]] of the [[Taça de Portugal]], played on 28 May 2017, Semedo assisted [[Eduardo Salvio]] for the second goal, with Benfica lifting the trophy after defeating [[Vitória S.C.|Vitória de Guimarães]] 2–1.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.maisfutebol.iol.pt/vitoria-guimaraes/final/benfica-conquista-26-taca-de-portugal|title=Benfica conquista 26ª Taça de Portugal|trans-title=Benfica win 26th Portuguese Cup|publisher=Maisfutebol|language=pt|date=28 May 2017|access-date=7 June 2017}}</ref> For his performances throughout the season, he won the Breakthrough Player of the Year award from the [[Liga Portuguesa de Futebol Profissional]].<ref name=Award>{{cite news|url=http://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/liga-nos/benfica/detalhe/nelson-semedo-vence-premio-revelacao-relativo-a-temporada-201617.html|title=Nélson Semedo vence prémio revelação relativo à temporada 2016/17|trans-title=Nélson Semedo wins breakthrough award for the 2016/17 season|newspaper=Record|language=pt|date=7 July 2017|access-date=7 July 2017|archive-date=8 July 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170708001409/http://www.record.pt/futebol/futebol-nacional/liga-nos/benfica/detalhe/nelson-semedo-vence-premio-revelacao-relativo-a-temporada-201617.html|url-status=dead}}</ref>

===Barcelona===
On 13 July 2017, [[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]] announced an agreement with Benfica for Semedo's signing, pending medical tests.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fcbarcelona.com/football/first-team/news/2017-2018/agreement-with-benfica-for-nelson-semedo|title=Agreement reached between FC Barcelona and Benfica on Nélson Semedo transfer|publisher=FC Barcelona|date=13 July 2017|access-date=13 July 2017}}</ref> He signed a five-year contract the following day,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fcbarcelona.com/football/first-team/news/2017-2018/nelson-semedo-arrives-in-barcelona-to-sign-with-fc-barcelona-minute-by-minute|title=Nélson Semedo's first day in Barcelona|publisher=FC Barcelona|date=14 July 2017|access-date=14 July 2017}}</ref> with the Portuguese club receiving €30.5&nbsp;million plus another potential €5&nbsp;million for every 50 matches he appeared in for his new team.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://web3.cmvm.pt/sdi/emitentes/docs/FR65146.pdf|title=Comunicado|trans-title=Announcement|publisher=[[Portuguese Securities Market Commission]]|language=pt|date=14 July 2017|access-date=14 July 2017|archive-date=9 August 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170809000823/http://web3.cmvm.pt/sdi/emitentes/docs/FR65146.pdf|url-status=dead}}</ref> He made his debut on 16 August in [[2017 Supercopa de España#Second leg|second leg]] of the [[Supercopa de España]] against [[Real Madrid CF|Real Madrid]], losing 0–2 at the [[Santiago Bernabéu Stadium]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/sports/dcunited/madrid-beats-barca-2-0-without-ronaldo-to-win-super-cup/2017/08/16/dbccfba4-82d7-11e7-9e7a-20fa8d7a0db6_story.html|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170817163710/https://www.washingtonpost.com/sports/dcunited/madrid-beats-barca-2-0-without-ronaldo-to-win-super-cup/2017/08/16/dbccfba4-82d7-11e7-9e7a-20fa8d7a0db6_story.html|url-status=dead|archive-date=17 August 2017|title=Madrid beats Barca 2–0 without Ronaldo to win Super Cup|newspaper=[[The Washington Post]]|date=16 August 2017|access-date=17 August 2017}}</ref>

Semedo made his Champions League debut for the club on 13 September 2017 and was praised for his performance during the [[2017–18 UEFA Champions League group stage#Group D|3–0 group stage win]] over [[Juventus FC|Juventus]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.espnfc.com/blog/the-match/60/post/3201936/lionel-messi-scores-twice-as-barcelona-get-revenge-on-juventus|title=Lionel Messi scores twice as Barcelona get revenge on Juventus in UCL|publisher=[[ESPN FC]]|last=Marsden|first=Samuel|date=12 September 2017|access-date=13 September 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.squawka.com/news/semedo-is-the-transformative-signing-barca-craved-five-things-learned-from-barcelona-3-0-juventus-analysis/990372#HRTPUtqEmtDBeYET.99|title=Semedo is the transformative signing Barca craved: Five things learned from Barcelona 3–0 Juventus|publisher=Squawka|last=Butt|first=Muhammad|date=13 September 2017|access-date=15 September 2017}}</ref> He scored his first competitive goal for the [[Catalonia|Catalans]] – and in [[La Liga]] – on 27 January 2019 in a 2–0 away victory against [[Girona FC|Girona]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.sport-english.com/en/news/barca/girona-0-2-barcelona-semedo-and-messi-on-his-comeback-do-the-business-7269603|title=Girona 0–2 Barcelona: Semedo and Messi on his comeback do the business|newspaper=[[Sport (Spanish newspaper)|Sport]]|last=Bona|first=German|date=27 January 2019|access-date=27 January 2019|archive-date=28 January 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190128082718/https://www.sport-english.com/en/news/barca/girona-0-2-barcelona-semedo-and-messi-on-his-comeback-do-the-business-7269603|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.marca.com/en/football/barcelona/2019/01/27/5c4de2f2e2704e5e958b45e9.html|title=Semedo gets his first goal in Barcelona colours|newspaper=[[Marca (newspaper)|Marca]]|last1=Aldunate|first1=Ramiro|last2=Clancy|first2=Conor|date=27 January 2019|access-date=27 January 2019}}</ref>
His second goal came against [[Deportivo Alavés|Alavés]] in a 5–0 win in the season's final match.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/report?gameId=550235 |title=Dethroned Barcelona ride Messi, beat Alaves 5–0 on final day of La Liga |publisher=ESPN |date=19 July 2020 }}</ref>

===Wolverhampton Wanderers===
[[File:Nelsom Semedo.png|thumb|right|175px|Semedo lines up for Wolverhampton Wanderers (March 2024)]]On 23 September 2020, Semedo moved to English [[Premier League]] club [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton Wanderers]] in a three-year contract (with an option of two further years)<ref>{{cite web |title=Wolves sign Semedo |url=https://www.wolves.co.uk/news/first-team/20200923-semedo-completes-wolves-move/ |publisher=Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C |date=23 September 2020}}</ref> for an initial transfer fee of €30&nbsp;million (approx. £27.5&nbsp;million, with a potential further £9.2&nbsp;million in add-ons) paid by Wolves.<ref>{{cite web |title=Agreement with Wolverhampton Wanderers for the transfer of Semedo |url=https://www.fcbarcelona.com/en/football/first-team/news/1837922/agreement-with-wolverhampton-wanderers-for-the-transfer-of-semedo |publisher=FC Barcelona|date=23 September 2020}}</ref>

Semedo made his debut for Wolves and his first appearance in the Premier League in a 4–0 defeat away to [[West Ham United F.C.|West Ham United]] on 27 September 2020.<ref>{{cite web|date=27 September 2020 |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/54222443|title= West Ham United 4–0 Wolverhampton Wanderers|work=BBC Sport|first=Steve|last=Sutcliffe}}</ref> He made his debut [[Molineux Stadium|Molineux]] appearance for Wolves in the team's next Premier League match, a 1–0 victory over [[Fulham F.C.|Fulham]] on 4 October 2020. He scored his first Wolves goal in head coach [[Nuno Espírito Santo]]'s final game in charge, the final game of the [[2020–21 Premier League]] season, a 1–2 home defeat to [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]] on 23 May 2021.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/57132113 |title=Wolves 1–2 Manchester United: Nuno Espirito Santo beaten in final game|work=BBC Sport|first=Gary|last=Rose|date=23 May 2021|access-date=23 May 2021}}</ref>

Semedo suffered a hamstring injury in Wolves's game away to [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]] in the Premier League on 24 February 2022; it was subsequently evaluated that the injury would keep him from returning to action for between four and eight weeks.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.molineux.news/news/nelson-semedo-set-to-be-out-for-4-8-weeks-with-hamstring-injury/|title=Nelson Semedo set to be out for 4–8 weeks with hamstring injury|publisher=Molineux News|first=Tom|last=Procter|date=3 March 2022|access-date=3 March 2022}}</ref> He had played in 23 of Wolves's 25 Premier League games in the [[2021–22 Premier League|2021–22 season]] at the point he sustained this injury. Semedo ultimately returned to first-team action on 24 April 2022 in a Premier League game at [[Burnley F.C.|Burnley]], playing the full 90 minutes plus stoppage time.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/61131377|title=Burnley 1–0 Wolverhampton Wanderers: Matej Vydra scores to boost Premier League survival bid|work=BBC Sport|first=Jonathan|last=Jurejko|date=24 April 2022|access-date=25 April 2022}}</ref>

On 19 May 2023, it was announced that Wolves had triggered a two-year extension clause in Semedo's contract, to keep him at the club until 2025.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/articles/c51p9n9y420o|title=Wolves: Nelson Semedo contract extension triggered|work=BBC Sport|date=19 May 2023|access-date=29 May 2023}}</ref>

On 16 January 2024, Semedo scored his first goal for Wolves in two years, in a 3–2 [[F.A. Cup]] Third Round replay victory over [[Brentford F.C.|Brentford]] at Molineux.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/67984477|title=Wolverhampton Wanderers 3–2 Brentford: Wolves set up FA Cup tie with West Brom|first=Simon|last=Stone|work=BBC Sport|date=16 January 2024}}</ref> His previous club goal had also come in the F.A. Cup, against [[Sheffield United F.C.|Sheffield United]], also at Molineux, in January 2022.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/59911632|title=Wolves 3–0 Sheffield United: Wolves score in either half to make fourth round|work=BBC Sport|date=9 January 2022|access-date=16 January 2024}}</ref> The goal against Brentford meant Semedo had scored more goals for Wolves in the Third Round of the F.A. Cup (two) than he had in 114 appearances in the Premier League up to 16 January 2024 (one).

On 13 December 2024, Semedo was named club captain, taking over from [[Mario Lemina]].<ref>{{cite press release |title=Semedo takes over the captaincy|url=https://www.wolves.co.uk/news/mens-first-team/20241213-semedo-takes-over-the-captaincy/|date=13 December 2024|access-date=13 December 2024|publisher=Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|location=Wolverhampton|language=en}}</ref> Following the conclusion of [[2024–25 Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C. season|the season]], Semedo's contract expired and he was offered a new deal by the club. However, he opted not to accept it and on 30 July 2025, Semedo announced that he would depart the club after 5 years.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.expressandstar.com/sport/2025/07/30/its-been-such-an-honour-nelson-semedo-announces-wolves-departure/| title="It's been such an honour" - Nelson Semedo announces Wolves departure|publisher=[[Express & Star]]|last=Keen|first=Liam|date=30 July 2025|access-date=30 July 2025}}</ref>

=== Fenerbahçe ===
On 31 July 2025, Semedo signed a two-year contract with [[Süper Lig]] club [[Fenerbahçe S.K. (football)|Fenerbahçe]].<ref>{{Cite news |title=Ailemize hoş geldin Nelson Semedo - Fenerbahçe SK |url=https://www.fenerbahce.org/haberler/futbol/2025/7/ailemize-hos-geldin-nelson-semedo |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250731210356/https://www.fenerbahce.org/haberler/futbol/2025/7/ailemize-hos-geldin-nelson-semedo |archive-date=31 July 2025 |access-date=2025-07-31 |url-status=live }}</ref>

On 6 August 2025, he made his debut with Fenerbahçe in a [[2025–26 UEFA Champions League#Qualifying rounds|2025–26 UEFA Champions League third qualifying round]] first leg against [[Feyenoord]] as a substitute in 2-1 away loss.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://fenerbahce.org/haberler/futbol/2025/8/feyenoord-2-1-fenerbahce |title=Feyenoord 2-1 Fenerbahçe |website=Fenerbahce.org |date=6 August 2025 |access-date=16 August 2025 |language=tr}}</ref> On 16 August 2025, he made his [[Süper Lig]] debut against [[Göztepe S.K.|Göztepe]] in a 0-0 away draw.<ref>{{cite news |date=16 August 2025 |title=Göztepe 0-0 Fenerbahçe |url=https://fenerbahce.org/haberler/futbol/2025/8/goztepe-0-0-fenerbahce |access-date=16 August 2025 |publisher=Fenerbahçe S.K. |language=tr}}</ref> On 17 September 2025, he scored his first goal in the team and the league against [[Alanyaspor]] in a 2-2 home draw postponement match. 24 September 2025, he made his [[UEFA Europa League]] debut against [[GNK Dinamo Zagreb|Dinamo Zagreb]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://fenerbahce.org/haberler/futbol/2025/9/gnk-dinamo-zagreb-3-1-fenerbahce |title=GNK Dinamo Zagreb 3-1 Fenerbahçe |publisher=Fenerbahçe S.K. |language=tr |date=24 September 2025 }}</ref>

==International career==
[[File:New Zealand-Portugal (23) (cropped).jpg|thumb|Semedo playing at [[2017 FIFA Confederations Cup]]|249x249px]]
Of Cape Verdean descent,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.maisfutebol.iol.pt/selecao/cabo-verde/nelson-semedo-e-portugal-la-pescou-mais-um-tubarao|title=Nélson Semedo: e Portugal lá pescou mais um "tubarão"...|trans-title=Nélson Semedo: and Portugal fished yet another «shark»...|publisher=Maisfutebol|language=pt|date=13 October 2015|access-date=7 June 2017}}</ref> Semedo was called-up to play for the [[Portugal national football team|Portugal national team]] on 2 October 2015 for [[UEFA Euro 2016]] [[UEFA Euro 2016 qualifying|qualifying]] matches against [[Denmark national football team|Denmark]] and [[Serbia national football team|Serbia]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.abola.pt/nnh/ver.aspx?id=574379|title=Nélson Semedo convocado por Fernando Santos|trans-title=Nélson Semedo called by Fernando Santos|newspaper=A Bola|language=pt|date=2 October 2015|access-date=8 October 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151005190231/http://abola.pt/nnh/ver.aspx?id=574379|archive-date=5 October 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref> He earned his first [[Cap (sport)|cap]] in the latter match, playing the entirety of a 2–1 win at the [[Partizan Stadium]] in Belgrade.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.maisfutebol.iol.pt/selecao/selecao-nacional/nelson-semedo-e-a-estreia-e-um-sonho-tornado-realidade|title=Nélson Semedo e a estreia: "É um sonho tornado realidade"|trans-title=Nélson Semedo and the debut "It's a dream turned reality"|publisher=Maisfutebol|language=pt|date=11 October 2015|access-date=5 December 2015}}</ref>

Semedo was selected for Portugal's [[2017 FIFA Confederations Cup]] squad.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espnfc.com/fifa-confederations-cup/story/3140490/confederations-cup-squads|title=Confederations Cup squads|publisher=ESPN FC|date=17 June 2017|access-date=29 June 2017}}</ref> He played the last match of the group stage, a 4–0 win against [[New Zealand men's national football team|New Zealand]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fifa.com/confederationscup/matches/round=274633/match=300334887/match-report.html|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170504011629/http://www.fifa.com/confederationscup/matches/round=274633/match=300334887/match-report.html|url-status=dead|archive-date=4 May 2017|title=Portugal cruise into semi-finals|publisher=FIFA|date=24 June 2017|access-date=29 June 2017}}</ref> He also appeared in the third-place playoff against [[Mexico national football team|Mexico]], being [[Ejection (sports)|sent-off]] in the 106th minute as his team won the bronze medal.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fifa.com/confederationscup/matches/round=274643/match=300334886/match-report.html#nosticky|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170504000633/http://www.fifa.com/confederationscup/matches/round=274643/match=300334886/match-report.html#nosticky|url-status=dead|archive-date=4 May 2017|title=Portugal come from behind to finish third|publisher=FIFA|date=2 July 2017|access-date=7 July 2017}}</ref>

Semedo was named in Portugal's preliminary 35-man squad for the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.goal.com/en-gb/news/revealed-every-world-cup-2018-squad-23-man-preliminary-lists/oa0atsduflsv1nsf6oqk576rb|title=Revealed: Every World Cup 2018 squad – 23-man & preliminary lists & when will they be announced?|work=[[Goal (website)|Goal]]|date=17 May 2018|access-date=17 May 2018}}</ref> However, he was not selected for Portugal's final 23-man squad for tournament.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sbs.com.au/news/portugal-world-cup-squad|title=Nearly half Portugal's Euro squad to miss World Cup|publisher=[[Special Broadcasting Service]]|date=17 May 2018|access-date=17 May 2018}}</ref>

In October 2022, he was named in Portugal's preliminary 55-man [[Portugal national football team|squad]] for the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]] in Qatar.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.record.pt/futebol/selecoes/detalhe/cmtv-revela-lista-de-pre-convocados-para-o-mundial2022-conheca-todos-os-nomes?ref=HP_DestaquesPrincipais|title=The list of pre-selected squad for the 2022 World Cup: know all the names|publisher=[[Record (Portuguese newspaper)|Record]]|access-date=31 October 2022|date=23 October 2022}}</ref>

==Style of play==
Semedo is mainly known for his speed, ball control, dribbling and holding on the ball.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.whoscored.com/Players/296363/Show/N%C3%A9lson-Semedo|title=Nélson Semedo|publisher=Who Scored|access-date=6 June 2019}}</ref>

